<article>
    <articleinfo>
        <author>
            <firstname>Staffan</firstname>
            <surname>Olsson</surname>
        </author>
        <!-- add authors here -->
        <title>Repos administration guide</title>
    </articleinfo>
    <section>
        <title>Installation</title>
        <section>
            <title>System requirements</title>
            <para> Computer with internet connection. </para>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>What Repos needs to compile</title>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>Java 1.4+</listitem>
                <listitem>Apache ant 1.6+</listitem>
                <listitem>Maven 1.0+</listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
        <section>
            <title>What Repos needs to run</title>
            <itemizedlist>
                <listitem>Windows / Linux / Mac OS X</listitem>
                <listitem>Apache 2+ HTTP server</listitem>
                <listitem>... with mod_dav and mod_jk2</listitem>
                <listitem>PHP 4+</listitem>
                <listitem>Subversion 1.2</listitem>
                <listitem>Tomcat 5+ with connector from Apache</listitem>
            </itemizedlist>
        </section>
    </section>
    <section>
        <title>User authentication</title>
        <para>
            Authentication is configured a three different places:
        </para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>Apache configuration in the repository mapping</listitem>
            <listitem>Webapp authentication module (Acegi)</listitem>
            <listitem>PHP authentication scriptlet, in <code>login.inc.php</code>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>
            Only Apache actually verifies the login. Repos code only makes sure it has access to
            the credential, to be able to retrieve resources for the user.
        </para>
        <para>
            They all need to be configured with BASIC authentication, realm = repository root
            url
        </para>
    </section>
</article>
